                <h1>Understanding Lens Compression in Photography</h1>
                <p>Lens compression refers to the optical phenomenon where background elements appear larger and closer to the subject when using a telephoto lens. This effect enhances depth, making backgrounds seem more pronounced. Itâ€™s essential for photographers to understand lens compression to create dramatic and impactful images, especially in portrait and landscape photography.</p>
